The '''Tammuz-an space navy''' was a small armada governed by [[King/Legends|King]] [[Mon Julpa]] of the planet [[Tammuz-an/Legends|Tammuz-an]].

==Characteristics==
The [[Tammuz-an/Legends|Tammuz-an]] fleet comprised several squadrons of [[R-22 Spearhead starfighter|R-22 ''Spearhead'' starfighters]],<ref name="TCSWE">''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]''</ref> [[H-60 Tempest bomber/Legends|H-60 Tempest bombers]] and several frigate-scale [[Capital ship/Legends|capital ships]], representing the first and last lines of defense for the entire sector.

==History==
The navy was responsible for protecting both Tammuz-an space, as well as the [[Tammuz-an shipping fleet]]. Some time prior to the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], Mon Julpa recruited miner [[Jann Tosh]] into the fleet and enlisted him with a [[Captain/Legends|Captain's]] rank.<ref name="TCSWE" />

Around this time, the pirate known as [[Gir Kybo Ren-Cha]] attacked Tammuz-an with his stolen [[Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyer]], the ''[[Demolisher]]''. The Tammuz-an space navy fought valiantly against the Demolisher as well as Kybo's modified [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE fighters]], and successfully repelled the enemy attack.<ref name="TPOT">{{DroidsCite|The Pirates of Tarnoonga}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
A continuity error existed in the fact that the [[RZ-1 A-wing interceptor/Legends|A-wing]] and [[A/SF-01 B-wing starfighter/Legends|B-wing]] starfighters, seen docked in [[Hangar/Legends|hangar bays]] and flying through [[Realspace/Legends|space]] throughout the course of the series, were not produced at the time that the animated series is set. However, this error has since been addressed with a [[Retroactive continuity|retcon]], making them earlier designs of the same ships: the R-22 Spearhead and [[H-60 Tempest bomber/Legends|H-60 Tempest bomber]], respectively.

